.Dd April 28, 1999
.Dt JAIL 8
.Os FreeBSD 4.0
.Sh NAME
.Nm jail
.Nd imprison process and its descendants
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm jail
.Ar path
.Ar hostname
.Ar ip-number
.Ar command
.Ar ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm
command imprisons a process and all future decendants.
.Pp
Please see the
.Xr jail 2
man page for further details.
.Sh EXAMPLES
This shows how to setup a jail directory tree:
.Bd -literal 
D=/here/is/the/jail
cd /usr/src
make hierarchy DESTDIR=$D
make obj
make all
make install DESTDIR=$D
cd etc
make distribution DESTDIR=$D
cd $D/dev
sh MAKEDEV jail
cd $D
ln -sf dev/null kernel
echo "proc $D/proc procfs rw 0 0" >> /etc/fstab
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr chroot 2 ,
.Xr jail 2
